<p>A fragile ceasefire between Israel and Hamas largely held into its second day, allowing a massive homeward flow of displaced Palestinians and opening the door for scaled-up humanitarian relief across Gaza [france24.com#19][washingtonpost.com#26][dw.com#2]. Gaza’s civil defense said more than 500,000 people have returned to Gaza City since Friday, even as many found widespread destruction and basic services shattered [france24.com#18][nytimes.com#13][washingtonpost.com#9]. Aid agencies and the UN prepared to increase deliveries of food, water, medicine, and shelter materials, while warning that access and logistics remain challenging after months of extreme deprivation and a UN-declared famine in August [dw.com#2][theguardian.com#45][newarab.com#42]. Diplomatically, Egypt will host a summit</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/SZVLHF1yrTCzuM_BMdyfT9sKtgLTdezv6jgd-r4hMzZ5S3E5DIiBTOaFkO4_-N-YHW_77XUskOTegKohYd6bGba5S4Rpn2_0lrLSEn-jgkzbGvioTKtujSmy72nEUyEzqy2xILE31FDwAOxamCU7sPpmDpMkGc7m-0tZ78erltem58j7SR_jYZSzmsDJxNm0dvfK84qnTY9pH3iZrJiwQYgMj8tpuX2WSKXb7tZ9OT4Xpsr29wroPz_rC0gf4eVwUG1g9XQ5UeEFAG0' alt='Displaced Palestinians make their way north in Gaza as the ceasefire holds.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Return movement: Gaza’s civil defense reported over 500,000 people returning to Gaza City as the truce took hold [france24.com#18].</li><li>Aid scale-up: UN agencies expect to ramp up deliveries of food, medicine, and water as access improves, though hurdles remain [dw.com#2][theguardian.com#45][straitstimes.com#41].</li><li>Swap mechanics: Hamas is set to begin releasing the remaining 48 Israeli hostages—living and dead—on Monday morning, in exchange for 250 Palestinian prisoners moved into position by Israel [france24.com#28][firstpost.com#22][straitstimes.com#21].</li><li>Numbers clarification: The expected releases include 20 living hostages and 28 bodies to be returned, amid ongoing coordination between parties [timesofisrael.com#25][france24.com#28].</li><li>Security framework: Around 200 U.S. troops arrived in Israel to set up a coordination center for aid and truce monitoring; no U.S. forces are slated to enter Gaza [euronews.com#48][straitstimes.com#46].</li></ul><blockquote>Your courage has moved the world. - Steve Witkoff</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>United Nations/UNICEF: Aid agencies anticipate a significant scale-up in deliveries under the ceasefire but stress that the humanitarian crisis continues. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/oct/11/agencies-prepare-to-bring-aid-to-starving-people-in-gaza-as-ceasefire-appears-to-hold'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Hamas official (to AFP): Disarmament is out of the question even if Hamas steps aside from governing Gaza. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/palestinians-return-destroyed-gaza-homes-ceasefire-holds'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>Egyptian presidency: Egypt will host international leaders to finalize the agreement aimed at ending the war. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20251011-live-trump-expects-gaza-ceasefire-to-hold-palestinians-return-to-ruined-homes'>France 24</a>)</li><li>Israeli hostages’ families forum: Families expressed gratitude and hope ahead of the anticipated releases while vowing to continue advocacy until every captive returns. (<a href='https://www.timesofisrael.com/masses-expected-at-rally-as-hostages-set-to-come-home-families-thank-you-people-of-israel/'>The Times of Israel</a>)</li><li>Arab American Trump supporters: Supporters voiced guarded optimism about the ceasefire while warning it must hold to keep their backing. (<a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/middle-east/trumps-arab-american-backers-hail-gaza-deal-worry-it-wont-hold-2025-10-11/'>Reuters</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/gazans-stream-back-home-as-israel-hamas-ceasefire-holds3'>Gazans stream back home as Israel-Hamas ceasefire holds</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https